Arsenal have been in touch with Luis Enrique, as the pressure grows on Unai Emery, according to El Confidencial. The Gunners have won just two of their last 10 Premier League games and Saturday’s 2-0 defeat at Leicester City saw them drop to sixth place. During the game, fans kept chanting for Emery to be sacked. And now it has emerged that Arsenal have made preliminary moves to replace him. Head of football, Raul Sanllehi, is already on the hunt for a new manager and has spoken to former Spain and Barcelona manager, Enrique. Enrique has been out of football since leaving the Spain post earlier this year, before the tragic death of his young daughter, Xana. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.